  "prompt": "Is T-fal cookware oven safe?",
  "response": "T-fal cookware comes in a variety of types, and whether or not it is oven safe depends on the specific product line. Many T-fal pots and pans are designed to be oven safe, but the maximum temperature can vary by model. Generally, T-fal cookware with a stainless steel or aluminum base is often safe to use in the oven up to certain temperatures, usually around 350\u00b0F to 400\u00b0F (175\u00b0C to 200\u00b0C).\n\nHowever, T-fal's nonstick cookware may have different guidelines, as nonstick coatings can be sensitive to high temperatures. Always check the manufacturer's specifications or the packaging for the specific temperature limits and any other guidelines regarding oven usage.\n\nIf you're unsure, it's best to consult the user manual or T-fal's official website for the specific product you have.",
